a-linked-resource-container-version=3D"37" alt=3D"" width=3D"468"></span></=
span></span></p>
<p><br></p>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"DevelopmentFlow-EstimationGuidelines">Estimation Guidelines</h2>
<p>We follow agile sprints of 2 weeks each. One PI is 3 months or 6 sprints=
.</p>
<p><br></p>
<p>There are usually 2 levels of estimations we do:</p>
<ul>
<li><em><strong>Very high</strong></em> level estimate for release/resource=
 planning=20
<ul>
<li>This is done in t-shirt sizes. For consistency across program, followin=
g mappings are used. Include 30% contingency and system testing effort.=20
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">T-Shirt Size</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Approx Story Points</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">3XL</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">320</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">2XL</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">256</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">XL</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">192</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">L</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>128</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">M</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>64</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">S</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>32</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">XS</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>16</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">2XS</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>8</p></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">3XS</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd"><p>4</p></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div></li>
</ul></li>
<li>Low level or detailed estimate for sprint planning=20
<ul>
<li>This is done in SP (Story Points). We follow Fibonacci series for sizes=
 and for consistency use following guide to map to a timeline=20
<div class=3D"table-wrap">
<table class=3D"wrapped confluenceTable">
<colgroup>
<col>
<col>
</colgroup>
<tbody>
<tr>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Story Point</th>
<th scope=3D"col" class=3D"confluenceTh">Person Days</th>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">8</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">7-9 days</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">5</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">4-6 days</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">3</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">3 days</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">2</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">2 days</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">1</td>
<td class=3D"confluenceTd">up to 1 day</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
</div></li>
</ul></li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p>Story sizing includes dev + unit test + system testing, which is include=
d in DONE criteria. So typical story size could be something like</p>
<ul>
<li>5 or 6 SP for dev (Captured in <strong>Story Points</strong> field in J=
IRA)</li>
<li>3 or 2 SP for test (Captured in <strong>Original story points</strong> =
field in JIRA)</li>
</ul>
<p><br></p>
<p>Please plan only&nbsp;<em><strong>max 8 SP per dev per sprint</strong></=
em>.</p>
<p><br></p>
<h2 id=3D"DevelopmentFlow-MoreInfo">More Info</h2>
<ul>
